1) Accidental Release Prevention and Emergency Response Policies

Bercen Chemical, LLC (Bercen), is a chemical manufacturing, blending, and packaging company located in Denham Springs, Louisiana. Bercen's parent company, Vertellus, is a global supplier of specialty chemical products and is based in Indianapolis, Indiana.   Bercen complies with applicable federal, state and local regulations including OSHA's PSM standard. Bercen and Vertellus management are committed to the safety of employees and protection of our communities.  This includes Vertellus's commitment as a Responsible Care&reg; company.  This requires Vertellus to follow the highest regulatory standards across all of our manufacturing facilities.  Bercen has implemented numerous programs to both prevent and respond to accidental releases as follows

1) Employees participate in the development and execution of elements of the safety and release prevention program wherever possible;

2) Training on operations, emergency response, process hazards, incident prevention, mechanical integrity, and other programs is provided for operators and maintenance personnel;

3) Process Safety Information (PSI) is maintained on process hazards and made available to employees and other stakeholders;

4) A Process Hazard Analysis (PHA) of the process was conducted initially and is revalidated periodically to ensure adequacy of controls; 

5) The Mechanical Integrity program ensures the system continues to operate as designed;

6) Operating and Maintenance procedures provide operators and maintenance staff the information necessary to safely operate and maintain the system;

7) Contractors working on or near the ammonia system are selected for safety performance, and are briefed on the hazards and safety requirements of the job;

8) Hot Work Permits are required whenever welding, cutting, grinding or other activities are conducted that could generate sparks and start a fire;

9) The Management of Change (MOC) program requir

es that the impact of changes to the process be evaluated and approved prior to the work being conducted;

10) Pre-Startup Safety Reviews (PSSR) are conducted prior to restart of the system after modifications to ensure that impacts of the change are addressed;

11) Incident investigations are conducted for process incidents and near misses that endanger employees or the public, if such an incident were to occur;

12) Compliance Audits are conducted every three years to ensure that the prevention program is meeting its objectives;

13) Emergency Planning and Response ensures that employees are advised of evacuation routes, assembly areas, and responsibilities in the event of an anhydrous ammonia release or other significant process incident.  The local LEPC is involved in the Bercen emergency response program; and

14) Trade Secrets utilized in the manufacturing process at the facility do not interfere with the dissemination of pertinent PSM information about the covered process to operators, employees and/or the general public.



2) Facility and Regulated Substances

Bercen is an innovative specialty chemical company that designs, manufactures, and promotes chemical solutions. Our chemists, engineers, technicians, and sales representatives bring vast market experience to bear. Located in Denham Springs, Louisiana, the facility manufactures materials for the paper, fuel, lube, oilfield, and metal working markets. Core competencies include anhydride and derivative products, as well as specialty additives for paper making. Anhydrous ammonia is utilized as a raw material in the production process as a source of nitrogen and pH control. Ammonia is delivered to the facility by truck as a liquid and stored in a tank. Ammonia gas is used in the process.  



